The calibre of the 1966 and 1964 vintage on the Rhine and Moselle represents surely the best since 1959.

We happily present the famed vineyards and impeccable growers that have given German wines their great international reputation. Choose 1966 if you like your wines young, fresh and charming. Choose 1964 for added bottle age and a further touch of subtlety and complexity—some prefer this quiter, less fruity quality.
